OL,7,FSentencing Walid, Judge Linford
OL,8,Faccepted he had not entered the city
OL,9,F"looking for trouble" and that
OL,10,Fprotesters had been throwing missiles
OL,11,Fand making "deeply offensive racist
OL,12,Fchants".
OL,14,FHe said: "What you should have done
OL,15,Fwas rise above their simply obnoxious
OL,16,Fracism.
OL,18,F"You were capable of doing that but
OL,19,Fyou didn't, instead what you did was
OL,20,Fthrow four missiles of one sort or
OL,21,Fanother at the group opposite."
